CatDescriptText: Mrs. Susanna Cunningham, 1527 Brighton Road, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 30, 1958, pg. 3 with question: "Do you think that Negroes make full use of their voting franchise by registering and voting in both the primary and the general election?"  Answer reads: "I think that Negroes are doing their best to register and vote."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Susanna Cunningham wearing dress with dark satin trim, standing on sidewalk with pedestrians, storefronts, and Pepsi truck in background
